<br>
Personally, I play around with a combo of three different 1h'ers for aggro...SoD, BoC &amp; Agnarr's Sword.  Personally, I think the BoC is a piece of crap for initial MT aggro.   Yeah, the EB proc is top notch...but it takes the BoC a day to proc even with maxed dex.  In the time that it takes my BoC to proc, I typically would have a handful of SoD procs.  Is the Bloodfrenzy &amp; Hategiver that bad??  <br>
<br>
I typically start out fights while MT'ing with the SoD in mainhand and Agnarr Sword in offhand.  After a couple SoD procs, and some solid aggro, I switch in the BoC for the SoD for the extra 50hps and to maintain aggro.  Against a mob like Emp, where I dont get melee damage...SoD &amp; BoC the whole way typically.  Emp sticks to me like a troll to the swamp and the guild wizards love me.<br>
<br>
I still have yet to mess the 2h'ers while MT'ing...we haven't had a BBB drop from seru yet and we have yet to defeat RZ.  Most of the other 2h'ers just don't seem up to par with 1h aggro weaps.<br>
<br>
I was curious why the Agnarr sword wasn't listed though (or did I miss it?)...the 17/20 ratio (+1 magic damage), 125hps &amp; DD proc make it a damn nice offhander for main tanking IMO.  Or is it because the proc itself isn't traditionally an aggro generator?<br>
<br>
To each their own, I guess. <p>Arbok Bloodngutz<br>
